column4: <content>Bruegel: Lost Temptation of Christ. Cf. Drawing of this subject, pen & wash, Weimar, Staatl. Kunstsammlungen, Schlossmuseum, signed and dated 1573 (perhaps some echo of Bruegel), repr. [H.G.] Franz, [Hans Bol als Landschaftszeichner], Jahrbuch des Kunsthistorischen Institutes der Universität Graz, I, 1965, [pp. 19-67], pl. 84. Franz p. 43 notices connections with Bruegel 'large landscape engraving-yes- See also another drawing of this subject by Bol, Albertina Inv.7916, signed and dated 1574. Roundel. (*)(Photo adest)(Franz, Ibid., pl. 90) This latter probably closer to Bruegel, agreeing better with van Mander's description. There are also Temptations of Christ on Mountain by L. van Valckenborch. See A. Wied, Jb. Wien 1971.</content>
